    <div aria-hidden="true">
        <p>
            Capture3 is a C++ desktop application designed to capture and process photos. Originating as a research project, it delves into digital cameras, image processing, color spaces, OpenCV, and <span>multi-threading</span>.
        </p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <strong>Tethered capturing:</strong>
                Automatically capture photos with varying exposure values and focus planes without manual intervention.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Automatic color calibration:</strong>
                Detects a <span>X-Rite</span> ColorChecker Digital SG target in photos, computes white point and color matrix from patch values.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Exposure merging:</strong>
                Fuses photos with different exposure brackets to create HDR images.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Focus merging:</strong>
                Stacks photos with different focal planes for increased depth of field.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Color space visualizer:</strong>
                Preview images in RGB, HSB, XYZ, and LAB color spaces with 3D color space graphs.
            </li>
        </ol>
        <h3>Technical details</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Developed with <a href="https://www.qt.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Qt5</a></li>
            <li>Written in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C%2B%2B" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">C++</a>
        </ul>
